a) Why String is immutable in java and what is the difference between String and String Builder? And Write
some of the methods of String class at least 5 with example.

Ans:
The Strings are immutable in java because of security concurrency, class loading.
The String is immutable in java and the strings builder is mutable in java.
The method in string class are the inbuilt method which are used on strings.

Examples:
concat():concat string to the end of other string.

endWith():check the end with special Character

equals():compare two strings and return true or false


format(): Check the format and the argument in specified concation;

indexOf():Return the index of the string